text: S0 may refer to: * S0 Truss, an element of the International Space Station * Slok Air Gambia IATA airline designator * the representation of the number 1 in Peano arithmetic * ACPI S0 power state in computing * S0 galaxy, an astronomical code for barless lenticular galaxy * S0 (DIN 43864), an output from electricity meters that give pulses proportional to the amount of consumed energy * the S0 interface bus used in ISDN BRI in telephony ==See also== *SO (disambiguation)
title: S0
